Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.13,0:01:35.81,Top,,0,0,0,,Isabel, it's been a week already \Nsince we came to St. Clare's.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.81,0:01:37.08,Top,,0,0,0,,Yes, Pat.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.08,0:01:41.13,Top,,0,0,0,,A lot has happened, but it's still not that different \Nfrom the school we expected it to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.13,0:01:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I was surprised by how far ahead in the curriculum they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.10,0:01:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.01,0:01:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But with a friend, \Neven this place can be quite fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.24,0:01:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen surprised me with her kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.18,0:01:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Belinda Towers is full of surprises. \NNo wonder she’s the fifth form team captain. {lit: left me speechless}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.85,0:01:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But thanks to her you're on the lacrosse team. {lit: able to be active in lacrosse}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.05,0:01:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,True. But I still remember our vow. {lit: haven't forgotten}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.62,0:02:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The O'Sullivan twins \Nwill never fit in at St. Clare's!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.06,0:02:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.56,0:02:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.31,0:02:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll keep doing my best.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.36,0:02:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did I end up with a B minus in math? {meaning grades}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.21,0:02:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We're still not even close \Nto the bottom of the list... {/last place}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.61,0:02:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But we were number one at Redroofs!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.55,0:02:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.02,0:02:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone who got an "A" wouldn't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.20,0:02:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, don't sweat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.86,0:02:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s only because you two are newcomers, \Nwhile we’ve long since gotten used to St. Clare’s ways. {maybe go with "teaching methods"}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.46,0:02:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that really the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.60,0:02:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course! So cheer up, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.07,0:02:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary's such a nice girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.74,0:02:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.64,0:02:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, let's cheer up, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.98,0:02:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But we have French class next.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.21,0:03:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you think that teacher \Nis way too strict on us?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.15,0:03:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Mam’zelle, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.88,0:03:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,"C'est abominable!" {actually you're not supposed to pronounce that "t" in c'est but I guess no one told that to the Japanese VAs lol}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.35,0:03:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oh woe is me!" {actually nagekawashi is "abominable" in japanese but idk}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.52,0:03:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, exactly! {so alike}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.12,0:03:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, let's call that teacher \N"Mam’zelle Abominable!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.73,0:03:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.46,0:03:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And maybe we can think \Nabout something even more fun to do! {??? dunno what this is about and I don't like using "even" twice in one sentence but eh}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.23,0:03:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Such as... {/could it be}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.70,0:03:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,After tea time today...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.54,0:03:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! I can't wait! {/excited} \NIt'll be our first time since coming to St. Clare's...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.07,0:03:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to the movies!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.77,0:03:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Hooray! {/I'm so happy}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.58,0:03:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you say "movies"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.98,0:03:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,How dare you even consider that \Nafter handing in essays like this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.08,0:03:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,C'est abominable! \NOh woe is me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.59,0:03:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't French at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.82,0:03:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What on Earth have you been taught before?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.99,0:03:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,At our old school, \Nwe focused on conversations.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.89,0:03:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Our strong suit is speaking it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.99,0:03:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Patricia, Isabel, speaking alone \Nis not enough to understand French.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.15,0:03:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to study the grammar too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.12,0:04:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Regardless, no movies for you two. \NYou're rewriting this essay and bringing it back today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.74,0:04:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But... But we already bought the tickets, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.98,0:04:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care about your tickets!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.15,0:04:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What matters is for you two \Nto learn proper French.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.75,0:04:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what my job is!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.49,0:04:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, work through all the mistakes, \Nand hand it in again after supper.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.03,0:04:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Next is Hilary.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.23,0:04:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oui?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.70,0:04:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Très bien!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.17,0:04:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, next is Janet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.60,0:04:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oui!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.30,0:04:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, there were a few minor hiccups, \Nbut you almost got it. Keep doing your best! {???????}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.94,0:04:36.38,Thought,,0,0,0,,How cruel!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.38,0:04:39.78,Thought,,0,0,0,,We didn't refuse to rewrite it, \Nso what's wrong with doing it tomorrow? {lit: even though didn't say not to write}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.78,0:04:42.52,Thought,,0,0,0,,Instead, she denies us the movies \Nthat we've been looking forward to.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.52,0:04:44.35,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's the worst...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.96,0:04:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't wanna be \Non Mam'zelle's bad side, Pat! {lit: making Mam'zelle angry is a big deal}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.89,0:04:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I just poked a little fun at her once, \Nand she made me write down verbs after tea time. {https://jisho.org/search/kakitori - dunno what to make of it}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.98,0:05:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,For a full week, no less!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.81,0:05:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to the movies.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.52,0:05:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Pat! You can't! \NIt'll make a huge mess!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.54,0:05:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's stay and rewrite the essays...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.98,0:05:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm definitely going! \NAnd I'll rewrite the essay too, though it hurts. {????}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.25,0:05:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You should go too, Isabel!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.98,0:05:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.65,0:05:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Just slap something together \Nfor her during lunch. {lit: in the lunch break, just doing pappaa is enough - pappaa here is onomatopoeia for "quick and dirty" or something to that extent}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.29,0:05:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.96,0:05:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, let's eat now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.89,0:05:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.03,0:05:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.89,0:05:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll plan our nature study, \Nso please stay a little after lunch, okay? {literal, dunno what this is about}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.91,0:05:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?! I-Is it going to take long?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.57,0:05:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Relax, we’ll have it wrapped up before art class. I’m counting on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.87,0:05:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess we'll have to hurry even more, \Nafter art class.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.68,0:05:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Both of your sketches are coming along nicely. \NKeep that up when you turn them into finished pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.49,0:06:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, let's finish it off \Nwith watercolors today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.97,0:06:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, there's enough time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.14,0:06:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I was hoping to finish early...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.51,0:06:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It felt real nice when Miss Walker praised our pictures, \Nbut we almost ended up being {dangerously }late for tea time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.13,0:06:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, let’s skip tea and use this time \Nto rewrite our essays.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.60,0:06:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't be serious! \NI'm starving already.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.52,0:06:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Art class always makes me \Nhungry for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.46,0:06:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,While drawing that big apple, I almost felt like \NI could reach out to it with my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.63,0:06:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, the tea is waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.30,0:06:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.40,0:06:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! I'm coming too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.34,0:06:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet, this plum jam is amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.35,0:06:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,My grandma sent it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.31,0:06:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandma's jam is the best in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.88,0:07:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? But I was sure our mum's jam \Nwas the best in the world. Right, Isabel?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.09,0:07:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh? Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.02,0:07:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? How about you try it, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.53,0:07:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't mind if I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.86,0:07:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, look at the clock. {lit: it's time}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.33,0:07:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yikes!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.97,0:07:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.50,0:07:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Could they still be going out? {lit: those guys, don't tell me...}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.51,0:07:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to the movies.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.70,0:07:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.48,0:07:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We mustn't go.\NMam’zelle will be totally livid when she finds out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.45,0:07:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I said I would go, so I'm going! {reworded to be less clunky}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.92,0:07:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't go, Pat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.80,0:07:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, I have an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.69,0:07:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Look: Mam’zelle told us to resubmit it after supper, \Nbut she never said when. {/after dinner}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.28,0:07:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.23,0:07:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,When everyone goes to bed, \Nwe'll slip out in our nightgowns.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.90,0:07:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll correct the essay in the study room \Nand take it to Mam’zelle. {maybe "will take it to mamzelle's class" will see}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.07,0:07:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No way we can do that! In our gowns \Nin the middle of the night? Are you nuts? {??}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.30,0:08:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Mam'zelle's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.48,0:08:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, we didn't wanna \Ncome to St. Clare's in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.92,0:08:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They could expel us and I wouldn't care.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.70,0:08:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you say that, Pat...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.30,0:08:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you thought about \Nwhat Dad and Mum would say?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.26,0:08:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they'll finally realize \Nsending us to this school was a mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.20,0:08:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, what would the girls \Nback at Redroofs think?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.00,0:08:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.89,0:08:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough about that. I made up my mind. {lit: my feelings won't change}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.17,0:08:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’re not coming, \Ngo ahead and play the good girl by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.86,0:08:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.76,0:08:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Going to the movies, twins? \NThat must mean you finished your French essays. {lit: did your french}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.24,0:08:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Not yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.77,0:08:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You girls must really be fools.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.12,0:08:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Why make things more difficult \Nthan they need to be for no reason? {to insist on one's own ideas}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.86,0:09:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, we need to head back soon, \Nlest we be late for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.36,0:09:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.64,0:09:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I still feel uneasy somehow, \Nas if we never went to that movie. {????}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.31,0:09:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.38,0:09:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, lights out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.31,0:09:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? But where's Miss Roberts? {meaning she's supposed to come and announce lights out}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.72,0:09:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,She said she needed to go see the headmistress, \Nso I'm acting as her deputy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.77,0:09:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So the teacher's not coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.77,0:09:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{Yahoo! }
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.02,0:09:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll regret it, Doris!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.76,0:09:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, really, Joan? {can't hear shit, from the book}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.40,0:09:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Why won't you give it a rest? \NI'm killing the lights!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.17,0:10:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.54,0:10:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We gotta gather them!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.20,0:10:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but time's up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.51,0:10:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Roberts will come to check on us \Nin about an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.10,0:10:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,C'mon, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.70,0:10:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! It's so hard to find them now! {lit: What're we going to do if we don't find them? - think she means it more as "we can't find them, what do we do"}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.02,0:10:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as if a cat's been chasing \Nhens in our dormitory! {in book:  Lights are going out now! Miss Roberts will be along to see we’re all right in an hour’s time, so let’s hope she won’t spot the feathers all over the place. She’ll think the cat’s been chasing hens in our dormitory}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.16,0:10:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You're all so sly, even though \NI'm the one who would get scolded for this! {??}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.76,0:10:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but we gotta sleep now! {?????}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.90,0:10:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.56,0:10:31.10,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Night!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.81,0:10:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.24,0:10:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if Miss Roberts comes? {[and sees that we're gone]}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.68,0:10:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We have no time to waste. \NIf Mam’zelle falls asleep, it's all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.79,0:10:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If we leave it like this, she won't notice. \NCome on, hurry now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.54,0:11:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.70,0:11:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,All quiet here. {lit: no abnormalities}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.62,0:12:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate those cumbersome \NFrench verb conjugations.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.76,0:12:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Why must we even learn French \Nin the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.83,0:12:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll finish it at any cost, \Nthen hand it in with my head held high. {/proudly/with my chest puffed out}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.43,0:12:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Won't Mam'zelle be angry \Nif we hand it in at such an hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.85,0:12:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,She won't have a leg to stand on! {lit: she's not supposed to complain}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.57,0:12:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,She said hand it in after supper,\Nand that's what we'll do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.65,0:12:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, done. \NSo, shall we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.05,0:12:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,My knees are shaking at the very thought! {of seeing mamzelle}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.26,0:12:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheer up, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.33,0:12:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.50,0:12:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.07,0:12:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? She's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.31,0:12:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe she's in her bedroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.27,0:12:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe she fell asleep already?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.08,0:13:04.75,Top,,0,0,0,,I think we should cover up to this point \Nin the current term. {/semester}{??? half-guessing}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.75,0:13:05.95,Top,,0,0,0,,Is that so? {soudesuka}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.95,0:13:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That's Mam'zelle's voice!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.05,0:13:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,She's in the fourth form classroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.19,0:13:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's someone else there, it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.16,0:13:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably Miss Walker, the art mistress.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.39,0:13:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,She's friends with Mam'zelle, \Nso it doesn't matter. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.87,0:13:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in. Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.14,0:13:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Mon dieu! Tiens! {https://www.thoughtco.com/tiens-vocabulary-1371402}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.98,0:13:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.85,0:13:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong? Are you girls unwell?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.07,0:13:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not that. \NWe've brought you our rewritten essays.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.22,0:13:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You said hand it in after supper, right? \NSo here we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.04,0:13:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Mon dieu!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.03,0:13:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But why are you doing it this late?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.93,0:13:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely, Mam'zelle meant \Nthat you should do it before bedtime. {sounds crude to me, but the headmistress was indeed calling her that in book too}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.57,0:13:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't have time to rewrite it earlier today... {/until now}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.95,0:13:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Such bad children!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.92,0:14:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You went to the cinema after all, \Ninstead of doing my essays!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.47,0:14:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Abominable!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.48,0:14:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress, these twins \Nmake my hair grey! The work they do!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.43,0:14:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And their French is all over the place!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.05,0:14:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It is impossible that they went \Nto a school before they came here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.79,0:14:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We did go to a school, \Nand it was a jolly fine one!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.56,0:14:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Much better than St. Clare’s!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.88,0:14:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.16,0:14:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we won’t decide \Nanything tonight, nor will we talk about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.94,0:14:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It is too late. Go to bed, twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.61,0:14:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And come and see me \Nat ten o’clock tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.54,0:14:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask Miss Roberts to excuse you \Nfor fifteen minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.01,0:14:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.55,0:14:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What bad luck to have run \Ninto Headmistress like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.34,0:14:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.70,0:14:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary? You're awake?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.73,0:15:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I woke up at the sound of Miss Roberts \Ncoming around to check on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.37,0:15:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Did she realize we were...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.74,0:15:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, she didn't notice anything. \NI did, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.04,0:15:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Where on earth have you been at this hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.58,0:15:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.89,0:15:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, I think you’re mad. \NYou behave like a couple of babies! {from book; dadakko = unmanageable child; spoiled child}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.32,0:15:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody would ever think \Nyou’d been head-girls at your old school.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.03,0:15:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night, Hilary.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.50,0:15:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.53,0:15:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night, twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.17,0:15:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,"Like babies"—can you believe it? {lit: [to call us] dadakko is harsh}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.34,0:15:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But maybe what Hilary said...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.15,0:15:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Was actually just right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.98,0:15:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, what's going to happen to us now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.89,0:16:00.99,Thought,,0,0,0,,To think it'd come to this...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.99,0:16:06.35,Thought,,0,0,0,,Rebelling against Mam’zelle is all fun and games... \NUntil it suddenly isn't. {book: It was all very well to be defiant and daring—but it wasn’t so funny afterwards!}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.35,0:16:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Come and see me \Nat ten o’clock tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.35,0:16:15.04,Thought,,0,0,0,,I wonder if Headmistress \Nwill write to our parents about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.04,0:16:18.38,Thought,,0,0,0,,What are they going to think about us?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.38,0:16:22.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,Why did I have to do something so stupid?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.16,0:16:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, open the next page now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.10,0:16:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Patricia and Isabel, don't you need to go? {lit: it's time}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.18,0:16:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.62,0:16:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.57,0:16:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.73,0:16:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, did you know? \NHeadmistress summoned them!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.90,0:16:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? {???}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.04,0:16:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Quiet, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.48,0:16:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What now, Pat?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.02,0:17:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,My legs are still shaking. {???? can't hear the action exactly}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.82,0:17:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had a lump in my throat \Nand my heart has been pounding all morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.19,0:17:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.91,0:17:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.61,0:17:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Sit down on that sofa and give me a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.95,0:17:38.69,Thought,,0,0,0,,Do you think Headmistress is angry?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.56,0:17:42.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,I wish everything that happened yesterday was just a dream...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.77,0:17:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I have been looking through the reports \Nthat your father sent me from your last school.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.36,0:17:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They had me properly impressed. {/outstanding results}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.24,0:18:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You seem to have been responsible \Nand conscientious children there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.98,0:18:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t imagine you completely changing your character in just a few weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.84,0:18:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So I am not going to treat you \Nas naughty, irresponsible girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.66,0:18:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I know there must be a good reason \Nbehind your queer behaviour from last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.30,0:18:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, my dears, you gave Mam’zelle and me quite a shock when you walked
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.60,0:18:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,into that classroom in your dressing-gowns.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.67,0:18:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress, the French teaching methods here \Nare nothing like at our old school.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.48,0:18:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't well expect one \Nto speak a foreign language perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.38,0:18:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Mam’zelle is simply too nitpicky. {lit: too strict about small things - persnickety}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.22,0:18:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened yesterday \Nwasn't our fault either!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.76,0:18:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole thing started because Mam’zelle blew up \Nover a trifle and ordered us to do the impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.96,0:18:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think, Isabel?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.36,0:18:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I do think Mam'zelle is a bit too harsh at times, \Nbut what happened yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.14,0:19:05.06,Thought,,0,0,0,,I wish I could say it was Pat’s fault, but that’d make me sound like I’m playing the goody two-shoes here. {lit: would make it seem like I'm the only good girl here}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.06,0:19:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you girls \Nwant to be in the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.53,0:19:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.44,0:19:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We haven't really...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.72,0:19:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,thought about it yet. {/know yet}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.96,0:19:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If you two were to become English teachers abroad, \Ncould you just sit back
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.16,0:19:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and ignore your students butchering the language?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.40,0:19:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we'd want to teach them proper English.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.17,0:19:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like Mam’zelle already had her sights \Non becoming a teacher when she was about ten. {I guess now we know how old they are in this show}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.08,0:19:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And she takes great pride \Nin being a French teacher now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.75,0:19:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What matters is for you two \Nto learn proper French.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.62,0:19:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what my job is!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.26,0:19:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You have not been well grounded \Nin the writing of French, it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.93,0:20:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Mam'zelle has offered to give you half an hour’s extra French a day until you have caught up to the others. {hoshuu = supplementary lessons}{also, from book}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.44,0:20:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Extra? {hoshuu}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.77,0:20:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All this bother has come from the fact \Nthat you were behind your class in one thing—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.28,0:20:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you are willing to work hard to fix it, \Nthere is no need to say any more about last night. {/we'll forget about last night}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.98,0:20:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Headmistress!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.52,0:20:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll try!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.72,0:20:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, go to Mam'zelle now and arrange what time \Nwill be best each day for the extra lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.60,0:20:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And don’t go marching through the corridors \Nin your dressing-gowns at half-past ten any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.18,0:20:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Headmistress!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.37,0:20:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that great, Pat?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.07,0:20:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We gotta thank Mam'zelle Abominable too!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.38,0:20:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We were rather the idiots yesterday. \NWe're really sorry! We won’t be again! {from book}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.00,0:20:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And thank you for saying you’ll help us \Nevery day with extra lessons!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.52,0:21:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now we'll see how clever you can be \Nat catching up to the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.56,0:21:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We shall be good friends, n’est ce pas?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.90,0:21:11.24,Thought,,0,0,0,,Although we really expected \Nthose extra lessons to be a huge pain...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.20,0:21:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Attention, Patricia! \NThis is not avoir. {??? beleving chatgpt, not in the book I think}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.68,0:21:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,"Tenir"? {/"To have?"} {入れ持って - not exactly avoir or to have, iremotte = take it in/hold it, but I think there's something going on here where pat uses the wrong french word (avoir), the teacher points that out, and pat says "[is] iremotte [the correct word here]" - but i have no idea why avoir is in french and iremotte in japanese, there's no way to tell what would be the correct french word this way lol}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.08,0:21:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactement!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.88,0:21:22.58,Thought,,0,0,0,,It was a stroke of luck! {lit: I'm glad we're receiving it}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.58,0:21:27.05,Thought,,0,0,0,,Mam’zelle is teaching us very carefully, \Nso we can understand everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.05,0:21:30.12,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's right. \NI feel that I'll grow to like French soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.12,0:21:31.99,Thought,,0,0,0,,Both the language and Mam'zelle, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.99,0:21:32.96,Thought,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.93,0:21:36.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.53,0:21:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Patricia and Isabel...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.14,0:21:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Très bien!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.21,0:21:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.58,0:21:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all thanks to Mam'zelle!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.48,0:21:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! She is a truly great teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.22,0:22:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.32,0:22:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I recalled what Headmistress said, and it made me curious what Mam’zelle must’ve looked like at ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.65,0:23:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Pat.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.65,0:23:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Isabel.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.99,0:23:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear? \NThe parcel of “fire-cracks” arrived for Janet! {from the book, dunno why not to spell it normally firecrackers but I'll go with this}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.54,0:23:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire-cracks?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.39,0:23:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! And she's going to put it \Nunder the desk of that timid Miss Kennedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.16,0:23:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, that'd surely make her jump in surprise!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.65,0:23:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But if it were me, \NI'd put them into the stove.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.17,0:23:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{imitating the crackling}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.60,0:23:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine the explosions!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.82,0:24:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time on The Twins at St. Clare's:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.32,0:24:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,"Janet is up to Tricks." {いたずらジャネット}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.32,0:24:04.83,Note,,0,0,0,,Episode 4\NJanet is up to Tricks {いたずらジャネット}{title of the chapter from the book, the japanese title (itazura janetto) would be more like "playful/naughty janet"}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.91,0:24:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
